main event: On 22 May 1955, multiple airmen observed unusual flying objects near Cheyenne, Wyoming.
interesting points: The objects displayed erratic movement not typical of balloons,The sighting duration varied from 10 seconds to 5 minutes,Objects were described as having white light and a dark purplish center,Four objects were consistently observed during the incident,The report was deemed 'unresolved' due to difficulty in radar tracking.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects (two silver-like objects, 4 objects including slender rectangular and oval shapes)
witness description: Airmen from Francis E. Warren Air Force Base
